race.comment: ZOU SENSATION (4) from their last start clash in the Listed Weekend Hustler at Caulfield. KING ZEPHYR started $1.65 there but got back on a day it was better to be on the speed, came wide and hit the line well. All his best form has been on big tracks and the middle draw at Flemington sets up perfectly. ZOU SENSATION is a good horse in his own right and maps for every chance. MEDIA WORLD (3) was okay behind Private Eye in the G3 Moonga Stakes last time out. He was well backed to win here prior and should get a good run on speed. The consistent WARNIE (6) was second in the Moonga albeit no match for the winner and should be right there again. NDOLA (14) is up a fair way in grade but drops 7kg and has come back very well.
